4.5 Requirements Specification

For this task, our group chose the subsystem ethics application creation, submission, revision, and tracking for a PhD student acting as the principal researcher. We think this is a suitable scope because it focuses on one clear part of REMS and matches our chosen stakeholder. This part of the system includes creating an ethics application, filling in the required information, uploading supporting documents, submitting the application, receiving requests for clarification or revision, checking the application status, and working with research teammates on the same application. The REMS brief explains that each research activity must have a clearly identified principal researcher, that applications must include a description of the research and its risks, and that supporting documents are required. It also explains that amendments or extensions may sometimes be needed after approval. For this reason, our chosen subsystem is an important and realistic part of the overall system
